main event: Multiple bright, oval-shaped objects were observed over Pequannock, New Jersey on May 9, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were described as red, orange, and green in color.
The objects were observed moving very fast from east to west, with at least four evenly spaced objects about one second apart.
The objects had no trail, tail, sound, or appeared to be subjoining or rolling.
The witness observed the objects for about 20-30 minutes, with the objects first being stationary and then moving rapidly upwards and out of sight.
Another witness provided a rough sketch of a similar object they had observed, describing it as traveling at an extremely high rate of speed and making no noise.
